                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions</label>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           <note>
                              <p>Folloing the colophon, The text on f.313b is a description of winter. There follow six
                                 unfoliated leaves on polished brown paper, containing a variant recension
                                 of the beginning of Dihistānī’s text. </p>
                           </note>
                           <note> Notes: on the fly leaf, saying that the book, which was defective, was
                              re-arranged and completed for William Hamilton in March 1863. </note>
                           <note> f.1a note. Muḥammad Hādī Ḥusaynī bought the manuscript in 1090 AH. His
                              seal is affixed. </note>
                           <stamp> f. 1a Seal of Fāz̤il Khān Murīd dated 1114 AH; Seal of Sayyid Khān
                              Ḥusaynī dated 1218. Stamp dated 1206 AH. </stamp>
                           <stamp> f.1b Ex libris of Sulaymān Jāh. Ex libris of Shāh ?Ramīn </stamp>
                           <stamp> f.313b Ex libris of Sulaymān Jāh dated 1244 AH. Owner’s note by Ṣādiq
                              Muḥammad Raz̤avī. Stamp of Muḥammad ʿAlī dated 1234 AH </stamp>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
